          </p>
          <p class="muted">
            During a recent internal audit, you noticed that the company’s Asian branch reports very large profits,
            but the local bank accounts do not show the same cash balance. The local managers say the money is held
            by a third-party partner, but they refuse to share official documents.
          </p>

          <p class="muted"><strong>Task</strong></p>
          <p class="muted">
            Write an email to your <strong>Chief Financial Officer (CFO)</strong> or <strong>Audit Manager</strong> to:
          </p>
          <ul class="muted">
            <li>Summarize what you discovered,</li>
            <li>Explain the risks to the company (financial, legal, or reputational),</li>
            <li>Recommend what action should be taken next.</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="muted"><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
          <ul class="muted">
            <li>Use at least <strong>three (3)</strong> vocabulary words from Section A.</li>
            <li>
              Follow a clear professional email structure:
              <em>Subject → Greeting → Body → Closing</em>.
            </li>
            <li>Use formal, professional language and write a coherent, well-organised email.</li>
          </ul>

